##Position                                                                           //position

its use for set your element position.
there is some of position availavale in css like

position: static/relative/absolote/fixed

1. Static: Its mean default position you cant chagne anything in it..

top bottom right left z index this is what we can control out position.
like if you want position will be in top 20px than you will select it.


2.Relative : its become relative now you can change anywhere in your page.
h1{
  position: relative;
  top: 10px;
}
now it will goes to top 10px.

3.Absulate:
it will follow the parents class
like you will use absulate in child class
and it will follow the parent class for positioning.

.parent {
  position: relative;
}
.child {
  position: absolute;                                                        //here is absolate
  top: 0;
  right: 0;
}

4.fixed: after using this your content will be fixed.
